From: dic@dcs.ed.ac.uk (David Chapman)
Subject: Kernel Paging Request failure with mtools
Date: Fri, 5 Nov 1993 17:24:55 GMT

When I am using mdir and mcopy, my machine crashes with the following error 
message about half the time.  It doesn't seem to happen whilst running any other 
programs.

Unable to handle kernal paging request at address C0000000

Ops: 0000
EIP: 0010:0010CF6C
EFLAGS: 00010287
eax: 0000059a      ebx: 00000000    ecx: 000003d5  edx: 001ac4b0
esi: 001dcd74      edi: 00001000    ebp: 001b5ce4
ds: 0018     es: 0018   fs: 002b   gs:002bn
Pid: 0, process nr:0

83 bb 1c 03 00 00 00 74 32 8b
task[0] (swapper) killed: unable to recover
Kernal panic: Trying to free up swapper memory space
In swapper task - not syncing

If I am running X, the machine sometimes just freezes when I am using mtools.  I
presume the same thing is happening, but the error message is hidden.

I am running a Dan 66Mhz 486DX2 with 8MB of Ram.  I have a VL-bus IO controller
which runs my single 1.44MB FDD, and my 2 IDE hard disks Drive hda is used 
for MSDOS, and drive hdb is used for Linux.  I have a 16MB swap partition (hdb6), 
and am running SLS 1.03 with a pl13 kernel.  The error message also occurred with 
the SLS 1.03 standard pl12 kernel.   I also have a VL-bus S3 card, and a Gravis
Ultrasound card, but the error occurred before I installed the sound card.


Any help would be appreciated.


David.

